title: Listen: Andrew Nemec talks Oregon Ducks, Oregon State Beavers football recruiting
text:
The Oregon Ducks and Oregon State Beavers have both landed four-star prospects in the past week, so the three-loss starts don't seem to be significantly impacting recruiting progress.
Oregon State has landed four-star recruits Christian Wallace and Shurod Thompson, but what's next for the program? Oregon still has a top 25 class, but has seen de-commitments from at least two prospects so far. Can the Ducks keep their top-end talent?
Also, given No. 3 Sherwood's 39-35 win over No. 2 West Linn on Friday night, what can we now say about the state title chances of those two programs?
The Oregonian/OregonLive's Andrew Nemec joined Judah Newby on 750am The Game to talk about these questions and more:
